1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:02,415
Welcome to Working with Firefighters.

2
00:00:02,415 --> 00:00:08,535
In IFS, firefighter parts often react
quickly when something feels too painful,

3
00:00:08,535 --> 00:00:10,496
too intense, or too much.

4
00:00:10,496 --> 00:00:18,159
They may distract, numb, escape, shut
down, act impulsively, or create urgency.

5
00:00:18,159 --> 00:00:21,967
This practice is not about shaming those
parts.

6
00:00:21,967 --> 00:00:26,379
It is about understanding what they are
trying to protect.

7
00:00:26,379 --> 00:00:29,305
Begin by settling into your body.

8
00:00:29,305 --> 00:00:32,091
Let your breathing be natural.

9
00:00:41,091 --> 00:00:41,091
<break time="3s" />

10
00:00:41,091 --> 00:00:43,088
Take a slow breath in.

11
00:00:52,088 --> 00:00:52,088
<break time="3s" />

12
00:00:52,088 --> 00:00:54,224
And let it out.

13
00:00:54,224 --> 00:00:56,082
Now gently ask:

14
00:00:56,082 --> 00:01:01,144
Is there a reactive or urgent part of me
that I can notice today?

15
00:01:13,144 --> 00:01:13,144
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

16
00:01:13,144 --> 00:01:16,488
This might be a part that wants to avoid.

17
00:01:16,488 --> 00:01:19,135
A part that wants to numb.

18
00:01:19,135 --> 00:01:22,386
A part that wants to distract.

19
00:01:22,386 --> 00:01:25,126
A part that wants to lash out.

20
00:01:25,126 --> 00:01:28,191
A part that wants to disappear.

21
00:01:28,191 --> 00:01:32,092
A part that wants immediate relief.

22
00:01:32,092 --> 00:01:35,575
Choose one firefighter part to focus on.

23
00:01:35,575 --> 00:01:40,080
Only choose one that feels safe enough to
notice right now.

24
00:01:40,080 --> 00:01:42,263
Now ask:

25
00:01:54,263 --> 00:01:54,263
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

26
00:01:54,263 --> 00:01:56,631
How do I feel toward this part?

27
00:02:08,631 --> 00:02:08,631
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

28
00:02:08,631 --> 00:02:14,854
If you feel judgment, fear, anger, or
shame toward it, that is understandable.

29
00:02:14,854 --> 00:02:18,801
See if you can notice those reactions as
parts too.

30
00:02:18,801 --> 00:02:22,238
Now gently turn toward the firefighter
part and say:

31
00:02:22,238 --> 00:02:24,792
I know you may be trying to help.

32
00:02:24,792 --> 00:02:26,928
I am not here to shame you.

33
00:02:26,928 --> 00:02:30,550
I want to understand what you are
protecting.

34
00:02:30,550 --> 00:02:31,943
Now ask:

35
00:02:43,943 --> 00:02:43,943
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

36
00:02:43,943 --> 00:02:46,822
What do you do when you take over?

37
00:02:58,822 --> 00:02:58,822
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

38
00:02:58,822 --> 00:02:59,751
Listen.

39
00:03:17,751 --> 00:03:17,751
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s"
/><break time="3s" />

40
00:03:17,751 --> 00:03:19,005
Now ask:

41
00:03:31,005 --> 00:03:31,005
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

42
00:03:31,005 --> 00:03:34,024
What are you trying to stop me from
feeling?

43
00:03:46,024 --> 00:03:46,024
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

44
00:03:46,024 --> 00:03:46,721
And:

45
00:03:46,721 --> 00:03:50,761
What are you afraid would happen if you
did not act quickly?

46
00:04:02,761 --> 00:04:02,761
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

47
00:04:02,761 --> 00:04:05,269
Let the answers come slowly.

48
00:04:23,269 --> 00:04:23,269
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s"
/><break time="3s" />

49
00:04:23,269 --> 00:04:24,755
Now ask:

50
00:04:36,755 --> 00:04:36,755
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

51
00:04:36,755 --> 00:04:39,077
How long have you been doing this job?

52
00:04:51,077 --> 00:04:51,077
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

53
00:04:51,077 --> 00:04:51,634
And:

54
00:04:51,634 --> 00:04:55,117
What happened that made this job feel
necessary?

55
00:05:07,117 --> 00:05:07,117
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

56
00:05:07,117 --> 00:05:10,275
You do not have to go into every memory.

57
00:05:10,275 --> 00:05:13,572
Just notice what the part wants you to
know.

58
00:05:13,572 --> 00:05:17,334
Now see if you can appreciate the
protective intention.

59
00:05:17,334 --> 00:05:20,306
Even if the strategy has consequences.

60
00:05:20,306 --> 00:05:24,068
Even if the strategy causes problems.

61
00:05:24,068 --> 00:05:28,294
The part may be trying to keep you from
unbearable pain.

62
00:05:28,294 --> 00:05:29,455
You might say:

63
00:05:38,455 --> 00:05:38,455
<break time="3s" />

64
00:05:38,455 --> 00:05:41,009
Thank you for trying to protect me.

65
00:05:41,009 --> 00:05:44,724
I understand that you learned to act
fast.

66
00:05:44,724 --> 00:05:48,393
I want to help so you do not have to work
so hard.

67
00:05:48,393 --> 00:05:50,483
Now ask:

68
00:06:02,483 --> 00:06:02,483
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

69
00:06:02,483 --> 00:06:06,198
What would you need in order to trust me
a little more?

70
00:06:18,198 --> 00:06:18,198
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

71
00:06:18,198 --> 00:06:20,566
Maybe the part needs proof.

72
00:06:20,566 --> 00:06:21,263
A plan.

73
00:06:21,263 --> 00:06:21,960
Support.

74
00:06:21,960 --> 00:06:22,749
Boundaries.

75
00:06:22,749 --> 00:06:23,864
Reassurance.

76
00:06:23,864 --> 00:06:26,836
A different way to handle intensity.

77
00:06:26,836 --> 00:06:28,369
Now ask:

78
00:06:40,369 --> 00:06:40,369
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

79
00:06:40,369 --> 00:06:45,385
Would you be willing to pause for just
one breath before acting next time?

80
00:06:57,385 --> 00:06:57,385
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

81
00:06:57,385 --> 00:07:00,682
If the part says yes, thank it.

82
00:07:00,682 --> 00:07:04,490
If it says no, ask what it would need
first.

83
00:07:04,490 --> 00:07:08,855
Now imagine offering this part a small
alternative.

84
00:07:20,855 --> 00:07:20,855
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

85
00:07:20,855 --> 00:07:22,109
Not a command.

86
00:07:22,109 --> 00:07:23,642
Just a possibility.

87
00:07:23,642 --> 00:07:24,849
Maybe breathing.

88
00:07:24,849 --> 00:07:26,289
Texting support.

89
00:07:26,289 --> 00:07:27,496
Taking a walk.

90
00:07:27,496 --> 00:07:28,750
Using the app.

91
00:07:28,750 --> 00:07:31,304
Writing in virtual paper.

92
00:07:31,304 --> 00:07:32,883
Naming the part.

93
00:07:32,883 --> 00:07:35,391
Putting a hand on your chest.

94
00:07:35,391 --> 00:07:37,109
Ask:

95
00:07:37,109 --> 00:07:40,731
Which alternative feels least
threatening?

96
00:07:52,731 --> 00:07:52,731
<break time="3s" /><break time="3s" />

97
00:07:52,731 --> 00:07:55,564
Now thank this firefighter part.

98
00:07:55,564 --> 00:07:58,675
Let it know you are beginning to
understand.

99
00:07:58,675 --> 00:08:01,554
Take a slow breath in.

100
00:08:10,554 --> 00:08:10,554
<break time="3s" />

101
00:08:10,554 --> 00:08:11,854
And let it out.

102
00:08:11,854 --> 00:08:13,247
Return to the room.

103
00:08:22,247 --> 00:08:22,247
<break time="3s" />

104
00:08:22,247 --> 00:08:26,241
And remember: this part does not need to
be defeated.

105
00:08:26,241 --> 00:08:33,253
It needs to be understood, supported, and
gradually relieved of its extreme job.

106
00:08:33,253 --> 00:08:39,463
The firefighter is not the enemy. It is
often a tired guardian standing near an

107
00:08:39,463 --> 00:08:45,513
old fire. With patience, trust, and
support, it may not have to work so hard.

